{{Infobox person | name = Anne Brooksbank | image = | alt = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = 1943 | birth_place = Melbourne | death_date = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (death date then birth date) --> | death_place = | nationality = Australian | other_names = | spouse = [[Bob Ellis]] | children = [[Jack Ellis (writer)|Jack Ellis]] | occupation = Screenwriter, novelist, educator | years_active = | known_for = | notable_works = }} '''Anne Mary Brooksbank''' (born 1943) is an Australian writer. She has written a number of novels as well as scripts for film and TV.<ref>{{cite web|title=Anne Brooksbank|url=http://www.austlit.edu.au/austlit/page/A19709|website=AustLit|}} (subscription required)</ref>
She teaches screenwriting at The [[Australian Film, Television and Radio School|Australian Film Television and Radio School]].<ref>http://www.aftrs.edu.au/short-courses/screenwriting-for-film-online/w519</ref>
==Personal life== She was born in [[Melbourne, Australia|Melbourne]] and studied English literature and history at [[Melbourne University]] and painting at the National Gallery School before becoming a professional writer.
She was married to [[Bob Ellis]], with whom she occasionally collaborated.
