{{Infobox journal | title = Journal of Mathematics and the Arts | cover = | editors = [[Craig S. Kaplan]] | discipline = [[Mathematics]], [[the arts]] | former_names = | abbreviation = J. Math. Arts | publisher = [[Taylor & Francis]] | country = | frequency = [[Quarterly]] | history = 2007–present | openaccess = | license = | impact = | impact-year = | website = http://www.tandf.co.uk/journals/titles/17513472.asp | link1 = http://www.tandfonline.com/toc/tmaa20/current | link1-name = Current issue | link2 = http://www.tandfonline.com/loi/tmaa20 | link2-name = Online archive | JSTOR = | OCLC = | LCCN = | CODEN = | ISSN = 1751-3472 | eISSN = 1751-3480 }} The '''''Journal of Mathematics and the Arts''''' is a quarterly [[Peer review|peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] that deals with relationship between [[mathematics]] and [[the arts]].<ref>{{citation|title=Educational Research: Material Culture and Its Representation|series=Educational Research|volume=8|year=2014|pages=163–178|contribution=Olympification Versus Aesthetization: The Appeal of Mathematics Outside the Classroom|first1=Kathleen|last1=Coessens|first2=Karen|last2=François|first3=Jean Paul|last3=Van Bendegem|publisher=Springer|isbn=978-3-319-03082-1|doi=10.1007/978-3-319-03083-8_11|editor1-first=Paul|editor1-last=Smeyers|editor2-first=Marc|editor2-last=Depaepe|quote=And of course, there is the ''Journal of Mathematics and the Arts'', which is dedicated to the topic.}}</ref>
The journal was established in 2007 and is published by [[Taylor & Francis]]. The [[editor-in-chief]] is Craig S. Kaplan ([[University of Waterloo]], Canada).
