{{Infobox museum | name = Shaki Museum of History and Local Lore named after Rashid bey Efendiyev | native_name = {{lang-az|Rəşid bəy Əfəndiyev adına Şəki şəhər Tarix-diyarşünaslıq muzeyi}} | logo = | image = Şəki Tarix-Diyarşünaslıq Muzeyinin binası.jpg | imagesize = | former_name = | established = {{Start date and age|df=y|1925|09}} | dissolved = | map_type = Azerbaijan | map_relief = | map_size = | map_caption = Location within Azerbaijan | coordinates = {{coord|41|12|13|N|47|11|44|E}} | location = Mirza Fatali Akhundov Street, [[Shaki, Azerbaijan]] | type = [[Archaeology]], [[ethnography]] | visitors = | director = Yagut Jalalova | publictransit = | website = | collection_size = 5000+ | area = }} The '''Shaki Museum of History and Local Lore''' is a museum located in Sheki city of the Republic of Azerbaijan. The museum is named after the Azerbaijani pedagogue, writer and ethnographer Rashid Bey Efendiyev.
==History== The Shaki Museum of History and Local Lore was established under decision of [[People's Commissariat for Education|Commissariat for Education]] in September 1925. In 1980, the museum moved to a building, which was built as a barracks in 1895.<ref name="gomap">{{cite web|title= Rəşid bəy Əfəndiyev adına Tarix-Diyarşünaslıq Muzeyi|url= https://kataloq.gomap.az/az/all-poi/culture/museum/8b292882d56611e0ad4900226424597d|publisher= kataloq.gomap.az|language= az|accessdate=21 February 2018}}</ref>
The total area of the museum is 924 m² and 724 m² of it are reserved for the exhibition halls. More than 5000 exhibits reflecting the history, culture, ancient art forms, ethnography and cuisine of Shaki are exhibited in the museum.<ref name="azculture">{{cite web|title= R.Əfəndiyev adına Şəki şəhər Tarix-diyarşünaslıq muzeyi|url= http://www.azculture.az/r-f-ndiyev-adina-s-ki-s-h-r-tarix-diyarsunasliq-muzeyi/|publisher= azculture.az|language= az|accessdate=21 February 2018}}</ref> Nearly 3,000 of them are exhibited in exposition rooms.<ref name="shekitravel">{{cite web|title= R.B. Əfəndiyev adına tarix diyarşünaslıq muzeyi|url= http://sheki.travel/az/accommodation/1021-RB-Efendiyev-adina-tarix-diyarshunasliq-muzeyi |publisher= sheki.travel|language= az|accessdate=21 February 2018}}</ref> There are also stands reflecting participation of Shaki people in Great Patriotic War (1941–1945), as well as in [[Soviet–Afghan War|Afghanistan]] and [[Nagorno-Karabakh War|Karabakh]] wars.
Open door is held on the first Sunday of May each year, which means visitors can enter the museum free of charge.<ref name="shekitravel"/>
The museum consists of the following departments: * Nature * Ancient era * Ethnography * Azerbaijan Democratic Republic * Science, culture, health figures * Battle victory * Silking * Agriculture * Table and kitchen culture of Shaki * Lecture room
